Sure, here are some example sentences that use the Serbian word "smetalo" in different forms and positions:

1. *Smetalo* mi je što nisam stigao na vrijeme. (It bothered me that I didn't arrive on time.)
2. Juče sam *smetao* u komšiluku dok sam čistio snijeg. (Yesterday, I was disturbing the neighbors while I was shoveling snow.)
3. *Smetali* su mi buka i gužva na ulici. (The noise and crowds on the street were bothering me.)
4. *Smeta* mi kada mi neko seče reč dok govorim. (It bothers me when someone interrupts me while I'm speaking.)
5. Da li ti *smeta* ako otvorim prozor? (Does it bother you if I open the window?)
6. Ne *smeš* mi *smetati* dok učim. (You can't bother me while I'm studying.)
7. Molim vas da *ne smetate* ostale putnike. (Please don't disturb the other passengers.)
8. Ovo *smetalo* je odlično za čišćenje prostorije. (This cleaning tool is great for tidying up the room.)

I hope these examples help!